    "unit_type": "edited_selection",
    "label": "Two Fifteenth-Century Cookery-Books (Thomas Austin's edited compilation)",
    "scope_note": "The cataloged subject is Thomas Austin's exact edited compilation first published in 1888: two substantial culinary streams from British Library Harley MSS 279 and 4016, selective extracts from Bodleian Ashmole MS 1439, Laud Misc. 553, and Douce MS 55, and Austin's editorial frame. It is not one homogeneous medieval work, not the whole contents of any of the five codices, and not the 1964 reprint carrier, University of Michigan encoding, or repository XML. The five physical witnesses and every editorial or digital layer remain distinct in the linked lineage manifest."
